message.content:
**Steamdeck settings for close 60fps**

some of these settings might make you go "what, why?" but just trust me

Genshin settings
Display Mode: either 960x600 or 800x500. Lower has a slight loss in quality, but performance gain is exponential
fps: 60
v-sync: on
render resolution: 1 
shadow quality: medium
Visual effects: medium
sfx quality: medium
Environment detail: lowest-low (the lower the better, however lowest can look bad for pop-in, but gives you a very close stable 60fps)
anti-aliasing: taa
volumetric fog: off
Reflections: on
motion blur: low
bloom: on
crowd density: low
subsurface scattering: medium
Anisotropic filtering: x16

The lower resolution (800x500 *or* 960x600) is noticeable but we can fix it with steam deck's built in FSR.

This requires you to add an-anime-game-launcher to steam so you can launch it in gamemode.
This matters ***a lot*** for battery, and performance.

Framerate limit: 50-60 (setting to 50 will almost completely get rid of stutter for loading, but cutscenes will be out of sync)
This is the most important part, and you won't believe it till you see it
**Turn on manual gpu clock control**
For some reason just having it on will take your gpu usage from 95-100% down to 50%
you will have to toggle it off and back on again every game boot, for some reason
something about steamdeck and Genshin don't jive well with saved settings, and it won't remember to limit GPU, even if its set to on
you can have GPU frequency set anywhere from 1000-1600 and it's the same performance
then, this part fixes the blurryness
scaling filter - FSR (fixes resolution)
FSR sharpness - 1-5 (depending on preference I like FSR sharpness 1)
it will seem a little blurry at times, but it will run like a champ

**Steamdeck settings for close 60fps**

some of these settings might make you go "what, why?" but just trust me

Genshin settings
fps: 60
v-sync: on
render resolution: 0.8 (trust me this helps a lot)
shadow quality: medium
Visual effects: medium
sfx quality: medium
Environment detail: lowest-low (the lower the better, however lowest can look bad for pop-in, but gives you a very close stable 60fps)
anti-aliasing: taa
volumetric fog: off
Reflections: on
motion blur: low
bloom: on
crowd density: low
subsurface scattering: medium
Anisotropic filtering: x16

The lower resolution (0.8) is noticeable but we can fix it with steam deck's built in FSR.

This requires you to add an-anime-game-launcher to steam so you can launch it in gamemode.
This matters ***a lot*** for battery, and performance.

Framerate limit: 50-60 (setting to 50 will almost completely get rid of stutter for loading, but cutscenes will be out of sync)
This is the most important part, and you won't believe it till you see it
**Turn on manual gpu clock control**
For some reason just having it on will take your gpu usage from 95-100% down to 50%
you will have to toggle it off and back on again every game boot, for some reason
something about steamdeck and Genshin don't jive well with saved settings, and it won't remember to limit GPU, even if its set to on
you can have GPU frequency set anywhere from 1000-1600 and it's the same performance
then, this part fixes the blurryness
scaling filter - FSR
FSR sharpness - 3-5 (depending on preference)
it will seem a little blurry at times, but it will run like a champ
